From 82b915051d32a68ea3bbe261c93f5620699ff047 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mauri de Souza Meneguzzo <mauri870@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Revert "tick/nohz: Fix inverted return value in
 check_tick_dependency() fast path"

This reverts commit 82b915051d32a68ea3bbe261c93f5620699ff047.

With nohz_full enabled, the corrected return value causes the tick to
actually stop on isolated CPUs. This breaks GPU command submission and
display pipeline scheduling at login, resulting in a visual freeze.

Under rc7 the inverted return value kept the tick running on nohz_full
CPUs unconditionally, which masked the underlying scheduling issue.
Revert until the root cause is diagnosed.

---
 kernel/time/tick-sched.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/time/tick-sched.c b/kernel/time/tick-sched.c
index d1f27df1e60e..f7907fadd63f 100644
--- a/kernel/time/tick-sched.c
+++ b/kernel/time/tick-sched.c
@@ -345,7 +345,7 @@ static bool check_tick_dependency(atomic_t *dep)
 	int val = atomic_read(dep);

 	if (likely(!tracepoint_enabled(tick_stop)))
-		return !!val;
+		return !val;

 	if (val & TICK_DEP_MASK_POSIX_TIMER) {
 		trace_tick_stop(0, TICK_DEP_MASK_POSIX_TIMER);
--
2.49.0
